{
 "name": "RPlog_Full_Circle",
 "title": "Full Circle",
 "summary": "At The Mission's refugee relief center in a converted Mos Eisley warehouse, Doctor Crestian (the Caspian Presav), his daughter Atsvara (the twelve-year-old Biscuit Baron CEO), and the Horansi woodcarver Kasha Tabasuri share a meal of porf after a long day of charity work. They trade stories of the clinic and the famine relief before turning to planning an upcoming charity auction, with Kasha donating hand-carved statues and Atsvara contributing a rare pre-Clone Wars Jolly Meal holocube. The conversation ranges across where to base Biscuit Baron's corporate headquarters amid the rivalries between the New Republic, the Imperium, and the Caspian Union, the antics of the droid Cricket, and the merits of locally produced toys. They reflect fondly on Tatooine and its sand, debating whether the world should ever be terraformed. The scene is a warm, reflective reunion that brings Kasha's long-ago year stranded on Tatooine full circle.",
